# Student Grade Calculator

A beginner-friendly Python project that calculates a student's average marks and assigns a grade based on the calculated average.

##  Features

- Accepts student name as input
- Takes marks for English, Tamil, and Mathematics
- Calculates the average score
- Assigns grades automatically
- Displays pass/fail status

---

## Technologies Used

- Python 3

---

## Project Structure

```
student-grade-calculator/
│
├── grade_calculator.py
└── README.md
```

---

## How to Run

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/student-grade-calculator.git
```

2. Navigate to the project folder

```bash
cd student-grade-calculator
```

3. Run the program

```bash
python grade_calculator.py
```

---

## Sample Output

```
Enter the Student Name: John
Enter the English mark: 85
Enter the Tamil mark: 90
Enter the Maths mark: 95

The average mark of John is: 90.00
Grade is A
```

---

##  Grading Criteria

| Average Marks | Grade |
|--------------|-------|
| 90 and above | A |
| 75 - 89 | B |
| 50 - 74 | C |
| 35 - 49 | Pass |
| Below 35 | Fail |

